8 PROPOSED POLICY COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
9 An Act relating to state government; creating the
Transparency and Accountability Platform (TAP) Act;
10 providing definitions; establishing TAP platform to
support a Supplemental Nutrition Assistance Program
11 (SNAP) Integrity Overlay and a Corrections
Transparency Overlay; authorizing the Department of
12 Human Services (Department) and Department of
Corrections (DOC) to procure and deploy the TAP
13 platform in coordination with the Office of
Management and Enterprise Services; clarifying the
14 TAP platform shall be a thin overlay and not require
replacement of core eligibility, supervision, or
15 payment systems; identifying purposes for which the
Department shall implement the TAP platform;
16 directing the Department to implement an initial
pilot program; authorizing the Department to expand
17 the SNAP Integrity Overlay statewide after completion
and review of pilot program; clarifying participation
18 in TAP-enabled processes shall be consistent with
federal SNAP eligibility; identifying the purposes
19 for which DOC shall implement the TAP platform;
directing DOC to implement an initial pilot program;
20 authorizing Department to expand the Corrections
Transparency Overlay statewide after completion and
21 review of pilot program; directing biometric
identifiers and templates to remain on participant's
22 or supervised individual's device; clarifying the TAP
platform may receive only nonbiometric cryptographic
23 assertions; allowing the Department and DOC to
receive and maintain nonbiometric data; limiting uses
24 and retention of collected data; directing the
Req. No. 16047 Page 1

1 Department and DOC to provide clear, plain language
notices; granting the Department and DOC rulemaking
2 authority; granting the Office of Management and
Enterprise Services certain technical and security-
3 standard-setting authority; directing the Department
and DOC to submit quarterly written reports during
4 pilot phase; providing required report contents;
requiring reports be made available to the public;
5 requiring the TAP platform be interoperable with
certain programs of the Department and DOC;
6 clarifying ownership of data; clarifying that the
Department and DOC shall be responsible for
7 oversight; prohibiting participants and supervised
individuals from being sanctioned, denied benefits,
